# CODEOWNERS - who is required to review changes to matching paths.
#
# GitHub auto-requests these reviewers on every pull request that touches a
# matching path. With branch protection's "Require review from Code Owners"
# rule enabled, their approval becomes mandatory before a merge - turning the
# review workflow from a convention into an enforced gate. Run
# scripts/protect-branches.sh to switch that rule on.
#
# Syntax: <path-glob>  <owner> [<owner> ...]   where <owner> is a @user or an
# @org/team handle. The LAST matching pattern wins, so order rules from general
# to specific. Paths are gitignore-style globs, rooted at the repo unless they
# start with a bare name.
#
# Replace @OWNER below with a real handle (e.g. @{{PROJECT_NAME}}/maintainers)
# before enabling code-owner review, or GitHub will reject the file.

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
*                       @OWNER

# Example: route specific areas to specialized reviewers. Uncomment and adjust.
# /docs/                @OWNER
# /.github/             @OWNER
# /scripts/             @OWNER
